    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ce4f4c17_8078588a",
        "filename": "libminijail.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 638,
      "author": {
        "id": 1136824
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-31T07:44:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027re right, I\u0027ve mis-read the API.  I\u0027m used to a non-portable strtonum(3) which returns an error string rather than characters after the parsed number.  strtoul(3) should be safe to use in this case, when negative numbers and suffixes are handled.  Notice that it is roughly the same amount of code, with the same amount of care about the corner cases ;-)\n\nOn Windows (anything else IL32P64 out there?) \"ul\" is not wide enough for a perfectly reasonable tmpfs size (4GB).  I\u0027ll use \"ull\" and verify the number accordingly.\n\nI\u0027ve also updated the tests for the now-impossible SIZE_MAX input value.",
      "revId": "6e8fb345487e99b601fbf7d1d62770c758d0b94d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
