      "writtenOn": "2017-01-31T07:44:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done.  All my pre-processor tricks to turn the value of SIZE_MAX into a string and then measure its length at compile time have failed, and without constexpr they started to get pretty nasty.  This is theoretically the largest number the user can enter, that we\u0027ll allow into the string (and, subsequently, into the kernel).  The ULL is technically not necessary but better than have an off-by-one stack overrun ;-)",
